reviewText: I used this workout when I was a beginner excerciser, and it was very challenging!  But, now I consider myself at a high intermediate level, I pulled this one out of the collection, and the weights, and the push-ups, and the lower body work are too short and are not a challenge, the aerobics will make you break a sweat, and raise your heart rate.  But not much of a challenge.  So overally this video is for beginners only, if you are not a begginer, but want weight work, try Jane Fonda's Toning and Shaping/Workout with Weights video, and alternate it with a video with more challenging aerobics such as the Lean Routine, which has an hour of aerobics with the option of High or Low impact or the New workout, which has 12/16 minutes of aerobics that is very very high impact.

reviewText: If you can get beyond the tacky clothes, big, big hair, corny video backdrops, and the annoying squealing voices (edited in AFTER the video was done), you'll find that this is not a bad workout video. There's both upper and lower body toning, you break a good sweat during the aerobics (which could be longer), and Jane Fonda does a great job explaining the moves. Decide between high and low impact, then follow the instructor in the lead. I bought this in a used bookstore, so I knew it would be dated, but it's also an aerobics classic.
summary: Corny 80's video, but it's a good workout !

reviewText: This is a really good workout for your lighter days, but do not be mistaken it is still a challenge.  This video has a weights segment, aerobics segment, toning and streching.  I have read other reviews that said this video was not a good workout.  They are wrong!  You simply have to take your personal intensity up a notch.  For example use hand weights in the aerobic section, and increase your speed while jumping higher.  There are two groups in the class a slower pace group and faster pace group.  Follow the group that best suits you. This is a great all around workout that lasts about an hour.  I would do the whole video to get a better burn.  And take the costumes and music with a grain of salt.  I would rather do a video with average looking people in dated clothes than some of these newer videos with uber fit perfect people in them.  Give this video a chance it is worth it.

reviewText: If only the upper body toning and the aerobics routine were a little bit  longer, this would be a perfect workout video. As it is, it's excellent.  The aerobics section is only 25 minutes aerobic. I'd prefer it to be 30  minutes or more. And I'll like either more reps or more variety for the  upper body toning. But the lower body toning is just great. Even with the  caveats, this workout will give you results. It's also fun and versatile.  You can increase the weights as you get stronger, and you can move from low  impact to mixed or high impact as you get more fit.  This one video can  easily last you all the way from Beginner to Intermediate.
